am\": \"UkraineBronze\", \"from\": 6912, \"to\": 6925}, {\"ngram\": \"the four canoeists\", \"from\": 6959, \"to\": 6977}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 6986, \"to\": 6990}, {\"ngram\": \"this event\", \"from\": 6994, \"to\": 7004}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold:Yarisleidis Cirilo Duboy (Cuba)Silver:Nevin Harrison (U.S.)Bronze:Lin Wenjun (China) Harrison won her first world title in 2019 at age 17.\\u00c2 Gold:Xu Shixiao and Sun Mengya (China)Silver:Ant\\u00c3\\u00ada J\\u00c3\\u00a1come and Mar\\u00c3\\u00ada Corbera (Spain)Bronze:Katie Vincent and Sloan MacKenzie (Canada) Xu and Sun struck gold when this event made its Olympic debut in Tokyo.\\u00c2 Gold:Lisa Carrington (New Zealand)Silver:Emma J\\u00c3\\u00b8rgensen (Denmark)Bronze:Tamara Csipes (Hungary) At 35, Carrington has already won five golds over the last three Olympics.\\u00c2 Gold:Emma J\\u00c3\\u00b8rgensen and Frederikke Matthiesen (Denmark)Silver:Paulina Paszek and Jule Hake (Germany)Bronze:Martyna Klatt and Helena Wisniewska (Poland) Paszek is a native of Poland, one of her pair\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s rivals.\\u00c2 Gold:New ZealandSilver:SpainBronze:Poland New Zealand\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Alicia Hoskin underwent heart surgery in 2017.\\u00c2 Gold:Ben Sav\\u00c5\\u00a1ek (Slovenia)Silver:Luka\\u00cc\\u0081s\\u00cc\\u008c Rohan (Czechia)Bronze:Nicolas Gestin (France) Sav\\u00c5\\u00a1ek has been in the top 10 of the overall World Cup standings since 2009.\\u00c2 Gold:Joe Clarke (Great Britain)Silver:Jiri Prskavec (Czechia)Bronze:Mathis Soudi (Morocco) French-born Soudi would be the first Olympic canoe-kayak medalist from Morocco.\\u00c2 Gold:Joe Clarke (Great Britain)Silver:Martin Dougoud (Switzerland)Bronze:Boris Neveu (France) Clarke angrily opposed his non-selection to the British team in Tokyo.\\u00c2 Gold:Mallory Franklin (Great Britain)Silver:Jessica Fox (Australia)Bronze:Kimberley Woods (Great Britain) Third at Worlds in 2022, Monica Doria could become Andorra\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s first Olympic medalist.\\u00c2 Gold:Jessica Fox (Australia)Silver:Ricarda Funk (Germany)Bronze:Maialen Chourraut (Spain) Fox\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s mother competed for France.\", \"from\": 7019, \"to\": 8709, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7062, \"end\": 7076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevin_Harrison\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nevin Harrison\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevin_Harrison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevin_Harrison\"}, {\"begin\": 7090, \"end\": 7100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Wenjun\", \"score\": 0.9999925976350132, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Wenjun\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Wenjun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Wenjun\"}, {\"begin\": 7102, \"end\": 7107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9575929010328041, \"rank\": 0.043533655811302016, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 7110, \"end\": 7118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Harrison\", \"score\": 0.8904919511110985, \"rank\": 0.09968496662344736, \"text\": \"Harrison\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Harrison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Harrison\"}, {\"begin\": 7171, \"end\": 7181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xu_Shixiao\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xu Shixiao\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xu_Shixiao\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xu_Shixiao\"}, {\"begin\": 7186, \"end\": 7196, \"title\": \