ustralia)Silver:Yang Hao (China)Bronze:Cao Yuan (China) Rousseau\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s grandfather, Michel Rousseau, won Olympic gold in cycling in 1956.\\u00c2 Gold:Wang Zongyuan and Long Daoyi (China)Silver:Jules Bouyer and Alexis Jandard (France)Bronze:Anthony Harding and Jack Laugher (Great Britain)\\u00c2 With 47 Olympic diving golds, China trails only the U.S. by two.\", \"from\": 11807, \"to\": 13299, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11848, \"end\": 11861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Friedrich\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lea Friedrich\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Friedrich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Friedrich\"}, {\"begin\": 11878, \"end\": 11891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathilde_Gros\", \"score\": 0.9999993327535274, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mathilde Gros\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathilde_Gros\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathilde_Gros\"}, {\"begin\": 11893, \"end\": 11899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.982649063452823, \"rank\": 0.010397389699777531, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 12009, \"end\": 12022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Friedrich\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lea Friedrich\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Friedrich\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lea_Friedrich\"}, {\"begin\": 12039, \"end\": 12052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martha_Bayona\", \"score\": 0.9999973065553043, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Martha Bayona\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martha_Bay