ram\": \"SwedenSilver\", \"from\": 15085, \"to\": 15097}, {\"ngram\": \"NetherlandsBronze\", \"from\": 15098, \"to\": 15115}, {\"ngram\": \"the one Olympic sport\", \"from\": 15144, \"to\": 15165}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 15175, \"to\": 15178}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 15183, \"to\": 15188}, {\"ngram\": \"every event\", \"from\": 15209, \"to\": 15220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold:Davide Di Veroli (Italy)Silver:Mate Koch (Hungary)Bronze:Romain Cannone (France) Cannone learned fencing on the Lower East Side of New York when his family lived in the U.S.\\u00c2 Gold:Tommaso Marini (Italy)Silver:Kyosuke Matsuyama (Japan)Bronze:Nick Itkin (U.S.) Itkin is the first U.S. man to win individual medals at consecutive world championships.\\u00c2 Gold:Eli Dershwitz (U.S.)Silver:\\u00c3\\u0081ron Szil\\u00c3\\u00a1gyi (Hungary)Bronze:Sandro Bazadze (Georgia) Dershwitz\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s maternal grandparents were Holocaust survivors.\\u00c2 Gold:ItalySilver:FranceBronze:Venezuela Rare South American medalist Venezuela scored one-point wins against Spain and Hungary for world bronze in 2023.\\u00c2 Gold:ItalySilver:FranceBronze:China Italy has the most golds in men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fencing, 39, one more than France, which has the most medals, 104, one more than Italy.\\u00c2 Gold:South KoreaSilver:HungaryBronze:U.S. Once-powerful Hungary won this event at seven straight Olympics from 1928 to \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009960.\\u00c2 Gold:Marie-Florence Candassamy (France)Silver:Alberta Santuccio (Italy)Bronze:Vivian Kong (Hong Kong) Hong Kong still competes separately from China at the Olympics.\\u00c2 Gold:Alice Volpi (Italy)Silver:Arianna Errigo (Italy)Bronze:Lee Kiefer (U.S.) Defending champ Kiefer married Olympic foilist Gerek Meinhardt in 2019.\\u00c2 Gold:Misaki Emura (Japan)Silver:Despina Georgiadou (Greece)Bronze:Yoana Ilieva (Bulgaria) No Japanese woman has won an Olympic fencing medal.\\u00c2 Gold:PolandSilver:ItalyBronze:South Korea These were also the standing at the 2023 Worlds.\", \"from\": 15232, \"to\": 16750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15273, \"end\": 15277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koch_people\", \"score\": 0.5502823344154646, \"rank\": 0.6654691843816815, \"text\": \"Koch\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koch_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Koch_people\"}, {\"begin\": 15294, \"end\": 15308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romain_Cannone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Romain Cannone\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romain_Cannone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romain_Cannone\"}, {\"begin\": 15310, \"end\": 15316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.6042105496691385, \"rank\": 0.5496030920924447, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 15369, \"end\": 15377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999998820453654, \"rank\": 5.172036277601196e-08, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 15456, \"end\": 15465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matsuyama\", \"score\": 0.6495328251379122, \"rank\": 0.5395673145901324, \"text\": \"Matsuyama\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matsuyama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matsuyama\"}, {\"begin\": 15480, \"end\": 15490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Itkin\", \"score\": 0.9999825433373252, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nick Itkin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Itkin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Itkin\"}, {\"begin\":