reat_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 26317, \"end\": 26320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9897425848735144, \"rank\": 0.010363720105405717, \"text\": \"GDR\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/East_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Great BritainSilver\", \"from\": 26213, \"to\": 26232}, {\"ngram\": \"NetherlandsBronze\", \"from\": 26233, \"to\": 26250}, {\"ngram\": \"Romania\", \"from\": 26251, \"to\": 26258}, {\"ngram\": \"31 Olympic golds\", \"from\": 26264, \"to\": 26280}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 26299, \"to\": 26307}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 26346, \"to\": 26353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold:RomaniaSilver:U.S.Bronze:Canada At 41, two-time champ Meghan \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMoose\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Musnicki will be the oldest U.S. woman to row at an Olympics.\", \"from\": 26357, \"to\": 26497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 26387, \"end\": 26393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.6323077683128695, \"rank\": 0.5162087918512199, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gold\", \"from\": 26357, \"to\": 26361}, {\"ngram\": \"RomaniaSilver\", \"from\": 26362, \"to\": 26375}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S.Bronze\", \"from\": 26376, \"to\": 26386}, {\"ngram\": \"41, two-time champ\", \"from\": 26397, \"to\": 26415}, {\"ngram\": \"Musnicki\", \"from\": 26435, \"to\": 26443}, {\"ngram\": \"the oldest U.S. woman\", \"from\": 26452, \"to\": 26473}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympics\", \"from\": 26484, \"to\": 26495}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold:FijiSilver:New ZealandBronze:Australia All three of Fiji\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympic medals have come in rugby sevens.\\u00c2 Gold:New ZealandSilver:AustraliaBronze:France The U.S. women could win its first medal in the sport.\\u00c2 Gold:Nicol\\u00c3\\u00b2 Renna (Italy)Silver:Luuc van Opzeeland (Netherlands)Bronze:Sebastian K\\u00c3\\u00b6rdel (Germany) Ethan Westera has an outside chance to win Aruba\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s first Olympic medal.\\u00c2 Gold:Matthew Wearn (Australia)Silver:Michael Beckett (Great Britain)Bronze:Pavlos Kontides (Cyprus)\\u00c2 Wearn considered a career in Aussie Rules Football.\\u00c2 Gold:Maximilian Maeder (Singapore)Silver:Axel Mazella (France)Bronze:Toni Vodi\\u00c5\\u00a1ek (Slovenia) Joseph Schooling\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s swim victory in 2016 is Singapore\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s only Olympic gold.\\u00c2 Gold:Bart Lambriex and Floris van de Werken (Netherlands)Silver:Erwan Fischer and Cl\\u00c3\\u00a9ment P\\u00c3\\u00a9quin (France)Bronze:Diego Botin and Florian Trittel (Spain) Lambriex won his first world medal at age 12 in the optimist class, set for young sailors.\\u00c2 Gold:Emma Wilson (Great Britain)Silver:Pilar Lamadrid (Spain)Bronze:Sharon Kantor (Israel) Emma Wilson\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s mom, Penny, sailed at two Olympics for Great Britain.\\u00c2 Gold:Anne-Marie Rindom (Denmark)Silver:Marit Bouwmeester (Netherlands)Bronze:Emma Plasschaert (Belgium) Now 36, Bouwmeester has won a medal of every color in her Olympic career.\\u00c2 Gold:Lauriane Nolot (France)Silver:Ellie Aldridge (Great Britain)Bronze:Daniela Moroz (U.S.) Now 23, Moroz won her first world title in China at age 16.\\u00c2 Gold:Odile van Aanholt and Annette Duetz (Netherlands)Silver:Martine Grael and Kahena Kunze (Brazil)Bronze:Olivia Price and Evie Haseldine (Australia) Haseldine coaxed Price out of her five-year retirement to chase an Olympic medal.\\u00c2 Gold:Caterina Banti and Ruggero Tita (Italy)Silver:Anna Burnet and John Gimson (Great Britain)Bronze:Eugenia Bosco and Mateo Majdalani (Argentina) Tita is both a computer-engineering nerd, and an extreme-sports dude.\\u00c2 Gold:Jordi Zammar and Nora Brugman (Spain)Silver:Keiju Okada and Miho Yoshioka (Japan)Bronze:Camille Lecointre and J\\u00c3\\u00a9r\\u00c3\\u00a9mie Mion (France) The 470 is being contested at the Games as a mixed event for the first time.\", \"from\": 26499, \"to\": 28643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 26533, \"end\": 26542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.7536213094999349, \"rank\": 0.28198882592992064, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 26649, \"end\": 26655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9968425333133738, \"rank\": 0.00291640843877353, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 26786, \"end\": 26795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Sebastian\", \"score\": 0.989314266272132, \"rank\": 0.01036869851283909, \"text\": \"Sebastian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Sebastian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Sebastian\"}, {\"begin\": 26805, \"end\": 26812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.9974920640956817, \"rank\": 0.0014316234771360856, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 26896, \"end\": 26909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Wearn\", \"score\": 0.999979956312579, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Wearn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Wearn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Wearn\"}, {\"be